Brokerage calculator
  • Call & Trade and RMS auto-squareoff: Additional charges of ₹50 + GST per order.
  • Digital contract notes will be sent via e-mail.
  • Physical copies of contract notes, if required, shall be charged ₹20 per contract note. Courier charges apply.
  • For NRI account (non-PIS), 0.5% or ₹100 per executed order for equity (whichever is lower).
  • For NRI account (PIS), 0.5% or ₹200 per executed order for equity (whichever is lower).
  • If the account is in debit balance, any order placed will be charged ₹40 per executed order instead of ₹20 per executed order.

List of charges
{/* Charges explanation section */}

Charges explained

Securities/Commodities transaction tax

Tax by the government when you buy and sell shares. It is 0.1% on both buy and sell sides for equity delivery. Only on selling side for equity intraday, F&O, and currency trading. Commodities transaction tax is 0.01% on sell side.

Transaction/Turnover Charges

Charged by exchanges (NSE, BSE, MCX) on the value of your transactions. NSE charges 0.00325% on equity, 0.002% on F&O. BSE charges 0.00275% on equity and 0.0001% on F&O.

GST

Tax levied by the government on the services rendered. 18% of (brokerage + SEBI charges + transaction charges).

SEBI Charges

Charged at ₹10 per crore by Securities and Exchange Board of India for regulating the markets.

DP (Depository participant) charges

₹15.34 per scrip (₹3.5 CDSL fee + ₹9.5 Zerodha fee + 18% GST), on the day you sell shares, irrespective of quantity.

Stamp charges

Charged by the Government of India as per the Indian Stamp Act for transactions. 0.015% or ₹1500 (whichever is lower) on buy side for delivery. 0.003% or ₹300 (whichever is lower) on sell side for intraday and F&O.

); } export default Brokerage;
